The paper deals with image processing and machine learning techniques applied to document images, which are typically categorized under computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of a novel Fully Convolutional Network (FCN) architecture for pixel classification also suggests a focus on deep learning (cs.LG, cs.DL, cs.AI) techniques.
